Peach Crisp
  --Sally McKenney

Preheat the oven to 350F (177C). Lightly grease a deep-dish 9" pie dish, 9" square pan, 10" cast iron skillet, or any 2–2.5qt baking dish. Set aside.

Filling:
5 c (~750–800g) sliced peaches (peeled or unpeeled)
1/4 c (31g) ap flour (spooned & leveled)
1/2 c (100g) granulated sugar
1/8 tsp salt
1 tbsp (15ml) lemon juice
1/2 tsp pure vanilla

Gently mix all of the filling ingredients together in a large bowl, then spread into the baking dish.

Topping:
1/2 c (100g) packed light or dark brown sugar
2/3 c (84g) ap flour
1 tsp cinnamon
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 c (113g) unsalted butter, very cold and cubed
2/3 c (57g) old-fashioned whole rolled oats (or quick oats)
optional: 2/3 c (95g) chopped or halved unsalted pecans

Whisk the brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, and salt together in a medium bowl. Cut in the butter using a pastry cutter or forks until the mixture is crumbly. Fold in the oats and pecans. Sprinkle evenly over filling. Bake for 45–50 min until the topping is golden brown and the fruit juices are bubbling around the edges. Remove from the oven, place on a wire rack, and allow to cool for a few minutes before serving warm. You can also serve room temperature or cold.


Notes: for gf, sub 1 1/2 tbsp cornstarch for flour in the filling & 1/2 c almond meal/flour in the topping
